public abstract class PbfGraphLoader extends BaseGraphLoader
A PbfGraphLoader loads data from PBF format into a GraphStore when Graph.load(GraphLoader, GraphConstraints) is called with a configured PbfGraphLoader instance. The source of data to read is configured by calling by calling dataSourceFactory(PbfDataSourceFactory, Metadata).

This base class contains configuration information available through configuration() that is useful to subclasses. Which ways and relations are included in the graph can be determined with PbfGraphLoader.Configuration.wayFilter(WayFilter) and a PbfGraphLoader.Configuration.relationFilter(RelationFilter). These filters must be explicitly provided by design and there is no default. This ensures that users of the framework think about which ways and relations they should include.

A region to clean cut against can be specified with PbfGraphLoader.Configuration.cleanCutTo(Region). Clean-cutting introduces artificial nodes when ways exit the region in order to cut the way exactly at the border. This is in contrast to "soft cutting" where ways that intersect the cutting region are not clipped at the border instead dangle outside the cutting region.
